name: stop
general_notes:
well’s criteria for dvt: {
        1: active cancer (1)
        2: paralysis, paresis, recent immobilization of lower extremity (1)
        3: recently bedridden for >3 days, or major surgery in last 4 weeks (1)
        4: localized tenderness along distribution of the deep venous system (1)
        5: entire leg swollen (1)
        6: calf swelling by >3 cm compared to asymptomatic leg (1)
        7: pitting edema (greater in symptomatic leg) (1)
        8: collateral, non varicose superficial veins (1)
        9: alternative diagnosis as or more likely than dvt (-2)
}

name: consider_lp

name: acquired_heart_disease
notes: e.g. kawsasaki disease with infraction, cardiomyopathy, myocarditis

name: trauma_and_brain_injury
notes: hypoxia, abusive head trauma, accidental trauma

name: non_infectious
notes: (extremely rare. always consider and treat for bacterial sepsis first)

name: bacterial_respiratory_tract_infections
notes: e.g.pharyngitis, pertussis, tracheitis, pertonsillar abscess, retropharyngeal abcess/cellulitis, cervical adenitis

name: intrauterine_insults
notes: e.g. congenital infections, fetal alcohol syndrome

name: crust/scab
notes: dried serum, blood, or pus overlying the lesion

name: scale
notes: dry, thin or thick flakes of skin overlying the lesion

name: lichenification
notes: thickened skin with accentuation of normal skin lines

name: artrophic_scar
notes: fibrotic replacement of tissue at site of injury

name: ulcer
notes: complete loss of epidermis extending into dermis or deeper, heals with scar

name: erosion
notes: partial loss of epidermis only, heals without scar

name: atopic_dermatitis_(eczema)
notes: age dependent distribution: infants: scalp, face, extensor extremities, children: flexural areas, adults: flexural areas/hands/face/nipples
